{"type":"text","timestamp":1773481814726,"sessionID":"ses_3144090b0ffeCEU4EeqeWovYRR","part":{"id":"prt_cebc0d4a2002Z1CpUU7RG6sSKq","sessionID":"ses_3144090b0ffeCEU4EeqeWovYRR","messageID":"msg_cebc0c8710010A7J3BtG012Ru8","type":"text","text":"All tasks are complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Summary\n\n**Task:** Replace F5 sort keybind with laptop-friendly alternative in `tui-browser.ts`\n\n**Problem:** F5 is used for keyboard backlight on many laptops, making the F5 sort cycling binding unusable without holding Fn.\n\n**Solution:** Replaced F5 with `O` (for \"order\") as the sort cycling keybind. The key `O` was chosen because:\n- It's mnemonic (\"O\" for order)\n- It was unbound — no conflicts with existing keybindings\n- It's on the home row, making it ergonomic\n- Tab still serves as the primary sort key when no wave is running\n\n**Changes made in `src/lib/tui-browser.ts`:**\n1. **Keybinding** (line 570): Changed `screen.key([\"f5\"])` → `screen.key([\"o\"])` \n2. **Status bar legend** (line 980): Changed `{gray-fg}F5{/gray-fg} sort` → `{gray-fg}O{/gray-fg} sort`\n3. **Header documentation** (lines 19, 27-28): Updated ASCII art status bar and keybind list to reflect the new `O` key and clarified Tab's dual role\n\n**Verification:** Both `bun run typecheck` and `bun run build` pass successfully.","time":{"start":1773481814725,"end":1773481814725}}}
